2. What is your day-to-day activities and what is the process and what is the role and responsibilities? So how you worked on it?

My day-to-day activities mainly involve developing and maintaining applications using Power Apps, Power Automate, Dataverse and SharePoint. 
First, I check the requirements from business users and understand what changes or new features they need. 
Based on that, I design or modify the Power Apps screens, forms, and logics.
I connect the app to the SharePoint/Dataverse as a data source, implement business logic, and test the functionality. 
I also work on role-based access, Data validation, and improving performance if needed.

Apart from development, I also handle bug fixes, performance improvements, and enhancements based on user feedback. 
I also work with Power Automate when there is a requirement for workflow automation like approval processes.

Overall, my role involves end-to-end development, automation, deployment, and support of Power Platform solutions.
At the end of day, I update task status in Azure Board and push my changes for review.
