9. In Power apps how to upload multiples files form SharePoint Library?

In my application, 
I upload multiple files to a SharePoint Document Library by using the Attachment control in Power Apps along with Power Automate. 
First, I add an Attachment control in Power Apps to allow users to select multiple files. 
This control supports multiple file selection using the MaxAttachments property.

Next, I create a flow in Power Automate with the trigger "Power Apps (V2)". 
In the flow, I use the Create file action from SharePoint and configure the Site Address and Document Library where files need to be stored.

Since multiple files are coming from Power Apps, I use an Apply to each loop in the flow to process each file individually. 
Inside the loop, I pass the file name and file content, and the Create file action uploads each file to the SharePoint Document Library.
This approach, all selected files are uploaded successfully to the SharePoint Document Library.











